<subSubSection id="C3796513FFE9FFF5FCF4FBA3FAD7157E" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BDC3698FFE9FFF5FCF4FBA3FAD7157E" blockId="1.[792,1418,1082,1299]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFE9FFF5FCF4FBA3FC49143E" bold="true" box="[794,923,1082,1107]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFE9FFF5FCF4FBA3FC81143E" box="[794,851,1082,1107]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Type</typeStatus>
data:
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFE9FFF5FC49FBA3FBB1143E" author="Schrottky, C." box="[935,1123,1082,1107]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="138 - 143" refId="ref4974" refString="Schrottky, C. 1908. Die bisher aus Paraguay bekannten Arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis und Hemisia. (Hym.). Zeitschrift fur Systematische Hymenopterologie und Dipterologie, 8: 138 - 143." type="journal article" year="1908">Schrottky (1908)</bibRefCitation>
proposed this variety of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D1BFFE9FFF5FCF4FBC3FC4F141E" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1901" box="[794,925,1114,1139]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Hemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burgdorfi">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFE9FFF5FCF4FBC3FC4F141E" box="[794,925,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">C. burgdorfi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
studying an undetermined number of females and males that belonged to the collection of Anisits collected in 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFE9FFF5FC73FB03FBDA14DE" box="[925,1032,1178,1203]" country="Paraguay" name="Asuncion" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Asunción</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFE9FFF5FBFEFB03FBAA14DE" box="[1040,1144,1178,1203]" name="Paraguay" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFE9FFF5FB6EFB03FA9C14DE" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[1152,1358,1178,1203]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref4557" refString="Moure, J. S.; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. 2007. Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S.; Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.). Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region, Curitiba, Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia. p. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFE9FFF5FB3EFB03FAD114DE" box="[1232,1283,1178,1203]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
were unable to locate the 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFE9FFF5FC10FB23FBE214BE" box="[1022,1072,1210,1235]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
series and unfortunately it was not found during the development of this article. Its current condition and depository are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3796513FFE9FFF5FCF4FAA3FADC16DE" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDC3698FFE9FFF5FCF4FAA3FADC16DE" blockId="1.[794,1419,1338,1715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFE9FFF5FCF4FAA3FC72153E" bold="true" box="[794,928,1338,1363]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Comments:</emphasis>
According to the information on the original description, the 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFE9FFF5FBEAFAC3FBE4151E" box="[1028,1078,1370,1395]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
specimens have two spots of yellowish pubescence on the mesonotum. However, the pilosity of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D1BFFE9FFF5FC2BFA03FB9515DE" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1901" box="[965,1095,1434,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Hemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burgdorfi">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFE9FFF5FC2BFA03FB9515DE" box="[965,1095,1434,1459]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">C. burgdorfi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very variable, being possible to find specimens with the dorsal surface of the mesosoma completely covered by blackish or yellowish pubescence, including intermediary forms. This species has been recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFE9FFF5FBFBF983FB51165E" box="[1045,1155,1562,1587]" name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(provinces of Misiones and 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFE9FFF5FCA4F9A3FC6C163E" box="[842,958,1594,1619]" country="Argentina" name="Corrientes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Corrientes</collectingRegion>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFE9FFF5FC3EF9A3FB44163E" author="Roig-Alsina, A." box="[976,1174,1594,1619]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="171 - 193" refId="ref4820" refString="Roig-Alsina, A. 2000. Claves para las especies argentinas de Centris (Hymenoptera, Apidae), con descripcion de nuevas especies y notas sobre distribucion. Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales, 2 (2): 171 - 193." type="journal article" year="2000">Roig‑Alsina, 2000</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFE9FFF5FB4AF9A3FB32163E" box="[1188,1248,1594,1619]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFE9FFF5FB02F9A3FAFD163E" box="[1260,1327,1594,1619]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Ceará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFE9FFF5FAD6F9A3FCBC161E" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Distrito Federal</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFE9FFF5FC97F9C3FBDE161E" box="[889,1036,1626,1651]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFE9FFF5FBF9F9C3FBB7161E" box="[1047,1125,1626,1651]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFE9FFF5FB9EF9C3FAD2161E" box="[1136,1280,1626,1651]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFE9FFF5FAE2F9C3FCB716FE" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFE9FFF5FC4BF9E3FBC716FE" box="[933,1045,1658,1683]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
states) and in 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFE9FFF5FB2CF9E3FAFB16FE" box="[1218,1321,1658,1683]" name="Paraguay" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
(Central and 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFE9FFF5FCA4F903FC4016DE" box="[842,914,1690,1715]" country="Paraguay" name="Guaira" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Guairá</collectingRegion>
departments) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFE9FFF5FBD2F903FAD616DE" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[1084,1284,1690,1715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref4557" refString="Moure, J. S.; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. 2007. Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S.; Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.). Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region, Curitiba, Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia. p. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFE9FFF5FB62F903FB1616DE" box="[1164,1220,1690,1715]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">et al.,</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
